cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper is primarily focused on Natural Language Processing (NLP) and its application in generating synthetic electronic medical record text. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper extensively uses machine learning techniques, specifically the GAN framework and the REINFORCE algorithm, to develop the model for generating synthetic EMR text. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper's focus on developing a model for generating synthetic EMR text falls under the broader umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the challenges of mining massive free-text electronic medical records, which raises ethical concerns related to patient privacy. 
5. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper discusses the limitations of using real EMR data for developing downstream ML and NLP methods and proposes the use of synthetic EMR data as an alternative. This falls under the domain of databases and data management.
